    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="262"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2583: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the Commission of Neutrals (<persName
                            corresp="#p_WF1" type="from">White</persName>) to the President of the
                        Council of the League of Nations (<persName corresp="#p_DVE1" type="to">De
                            Valera</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-03">December 3,
                            1932</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Neutral Commission has learned with pleasure through your telegram of November 25
                    of support Council is giving to efforts Neutral Commission endeavoring to bring
                    about peace in Chaco. Negotiations are progressing satisfactorily and Commission
                    hopes it will shortly be able advise you of distinct advances in peace efforts.
                    Commission has received your today’s cable and much appreciates your courtesy in
                    communicating to it text of Paraguayan and Bolivian replies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis White</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
